snippet: Jewish settlers moved early Tuesday into 26 apartments in seven buildings in a politically delicate, predominantly Palestinian neighborhood of East Jerusalem.
abstract: Jewish settlers move into 26 apartments in seven buildings in a politically delicate, predominantly Palestinian neighborhood in East Jerusalem; activists opposed to move describe it as largest influx of settlers into the area in decades.
lead_paragraph: Jewish settlers moved early Tuesday into 26 apartments in seven buildings in a politically delicate, predominantly Palestinian neighborhood of East Jerusalem.

headline.main: East Jerusalem Area Sees Influx of Jewish Settlers
headline.print_headline: Apartments Draw Jewish Settlers to East Jerusalem
